INFO:xe_forge.pipeline:  [2] suboptimal_tile_size: The GEMM kernels (_xproj_gemm_kernel, _dtproj_softplus_gemm_kernel) use small tiles (BLOCK_M=64, BLOCK_N=32) and num_warps=4. Intel XPU PVC prefers larger tiles (e.g. 256x256x32) and more warps for compute-bound GEMMs.
INFO:xe_forge.pipeline:  [2] missing_grf_mode: None of the kernels set grf_mode. For XPU large-tile GEMMs, grf_mode='256' (large register file mode) improves throughput.
