I added the fp16 round-trip (`dt_f.to(tl.float16).to(tl.float32)`) on the recomputed dt to exactly match the original behavior, where dt was stored in an fp16 buffer and re-read. This was the most likely cause of the numerical mismatch since the original SSM consumed an fp16-rounded dt while my fused recompute kept full fp32 precision, and the recurrence (with exp(-dt) compounding over L=2048 steps) is sensitive to small dt differences. Let me verify this corrects the output and improves performance by eliminating the dt buffer write/read and one kernel launch. 

